# Keep LF line endings in the working tree on every platform.
#
# Windows CI runners default to `core.autocrlf=true`, which rewrites text
# files to CRLF on checkout. Several assets are embedded into the binary
# verbatim via `include_str!` (e.g. crates/escurel-index/src/meta_skill.md)
# and parsed as markdown at boot — CRLF breaks that parse and the server
# fails to start ("the `escurel` meta-skill must remain valid markdown").
# Forcing `eol=lf` keeps those assets byte-for-byte identical across
# platforms; `text=auto` still lets git auto-detect and leave binaries alone.
* text=auto eol=lf
